Scale 1:2,990,000 (E 99°20ʹ--E 166°40ʹ/S 4°00ʹ--S 40°20ʹ). Sydney, N.S.W. : Printed at the Dept. of Lands, 1931 printing. 1 map on 4 sheets : color ; 150 x 186 cm, on sheets 79 x 105 cm cartographic image cri rdacontent unmediated n rdamedia sheet nb rdacarrier Also shows most of Papua New Guinea. "March 1931." Published as v. 3 of the author's The geology of the Commonwealth of Australia. Edited and much supplemented by W.R. Browne. [1950]. "Maps printed for Edward Arnold & Co." "Based chiefly on the maps published by the geological surveys of the states and by the Commonwealth Government, and on information supplied by the geological survey staffs, and by colleagues at the universities and elsewhere."
